title: okinawa guest house
address: Q5F5+76G okinawa guest house, Yangon
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Aung Hein Htun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl3XFbx9728FSecb30p5ArHzkOOjrbQCQ6DylJUzF3zwDP4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"BAD SERVICE, talks down on customers, has terrible staff, and the room arent clean. I would not recommend whatsoever! PLEASE avoid this hotel at all cost!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Exit H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We have stayed there 7 times and it is always nice to return. Being one of the first bunch of guest houses before they popped up like mushrooms 2 years ago Okinawa is a lovely place. Rooms are basic but have a fan or A/C. The bathrooms could use a bit of a treat though and the wifi could be faster / working in all areas. Breakfast is included in the price, varies every day and is being served on the tables in front of the guest house so you can watch the atmosphere around 32nd street. Sule Pagoda is 2 mins walk.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cello A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Good location, pretty close to the sule pagoda and chinatown, good breakfast and wifi but the staff is really confused and disoganized. I stayed in a shared room, when I come back to the hostel at night to sleep there was other people sleeping on my bed. My luggage was outside with all my belongings. The staff putted me in other room. I was really disappoitend. I could lost something!!! I got really angry but ok, I was in Burma. I suggest you to find other hostel to avoid this kind of thing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Janny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGX7ehkqfn6ZmkKzjxNzdDb6dHNMdA7FEE_BbTDHinkcdLPt5dVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Located less than a 5 mins walk from Sule Pagoda, it's a small guesthouse located on a small street in a busy area.  Lots of vendors, and you can purchase your bus ticket on the same street.  I booked one bed in a 4 or 5 bed dorm.  The mattresses were on the floor with a mosquito net.  Even though there was AC, it was still very hot at night.  I attract mosquitos fairly easily, and woke up to more than 10 bites all over my body, even though there was a mosquito net.  The bathroom kept running out of toilet paper.  The only pros about this place is the location, as well as the breakfast.  Otherwise, you pay for what you get here, and bring toilet paper.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Diane B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"One thing to be aware of is the mosquitoes. They acknowledge this issue by having mosquito nets for the bed but you have to do the work of making sure you are not bitten while you sleep. 1) shake the net off of sneaky mosquitoes--when we got there the net was hanging suspending from the bed and there were two mosquitos on the net and 2) once the mosquitoes are away from the bed, tuck the net under the bed so they don't get in. There was a single low lit light in the bathroom--had to use a flash light to see toilet, cold shower water and the sink water didn't work. The walls are paper thin and one guest kept banging on the door--lost his key or something. Good thing we only stayed there for an overnight and good thing we had our mosquito deterrent spray! If we stayed for longer the rating may be lower.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew O'Keeffe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6r-_DU84rALKi0a2Av9A2UbOkhdnP6bI8lxE3rvJKpeuHY7M_xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ok, so there are apparently two Okinawa guest houses. Both within 100m of each other. Review for this is for guest house number one.

The guest house appears to be run by children. The person checking you in is a 16 year old boy who's English is just enough to check you in. That's all. I actually made a booking from Agoda and apparently they had no record of it. But still had a room available. So lucky? I guess. The door to the room is an old fashioned Key and lock system that doesn't work without jiggling the door and key for 5mins to try find the sweet spot.

The rooms have no hot water. Only cold. The power shuts off in the rain and you'll get a torch to use in the room.

The bed has bugs and you'll wake up with bite marks over you. The bed and mosquito net both had blood stains on them. I ended buying a bed sheet myself to use while staying here from the local shopping. Also no wifi at all.

This is honestly just a terrible place to attempt to stay. There are a lot better options for the money. The double room was 25,000 Myanmar money for one night. So around $20.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Caleb F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Hotel staff were friendly. They let me have guests which some of the hotels don't allow. Room was clean, and well organized. Price was on the reasonable side for what I got. It was on the first floor which made it very easy to access. Plus it was relatively near everything. There was a cute little restaurant right beside the place with a sweet family that I ate at a lot because it was so cheap and such great food for that price. I highly recommend this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"florence l","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHwNVAhBufoo8LY9QJgA36LV2aF6lX0w2qy06Hm3sGcN-ZkjMp1R8g7n5EAkUzVe_g3g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed in the 2nd Okinawa (the one further from sule pagoda) thinking it was a good location : close from sule area and park but not too close from the pagoda 24h chanting mantras. |So it could have been a quiet place, if it was not fir the running teenage-team. No adults in here for the whole 2 days we have been in (so it is a very cool place for the young staff to work in!) But it then lacks of respect for the guests that wake up early and thus, go to bed early : singing loud, laughing louder, tv on...seemed to be in the staff house and not a guests house. The problem is the walls are very thin so you can't avoid the noise (We slept with ear plugs for 2 nights.)|Then dirty rooms (once more : teenage boys staff are often not the best to do this job!). Don't ever think to use the dusty mosquito nets if you tend to have allergy or are a minimum sensitive...|Good points though : breakfast, reception welcoming (also a teenage) and location.||To resume it is a good place for young people travelling on a budget (as Yangon is very expensive!!) but not much for thirties and/or older couples or single travellers that look for quiet places!!|","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jeremy B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We booked the Shwe War Guest House for our Yangon leg of our honeymoon based on the TripAdvisor reviews, and unfortunately were very disappointed. We are used to living rough - we stayed at a couple local villages with no indoor plumbing, minimal electricity, and felt the accommodations were much nicer than at Shwe War.||We would give the staff a sold 4/5 stars, but the facilities and experience were a generous 2/5. ||The Good||We loved the staff! Everyone was lovely, attentive, flexible and kind. We were greeted warmly and with smiles every time we arrived or departed the hotel. They were quick to accommodate all of our needs and allowed a late check out at no extra cost. |||The Bad||Breakfast was pretty terrible. I guess we shouldn‚Äôt have ordered the more western breakfast and instead opted for local fare, which may have made a huge difference. White bread egg sandwich with velveta style American cheese that had cucumber and...ketchup?||The room was roomy and had most everything we needed, but the bed was rock hard and we found ants on our comforter after arriving. We were told that we had probably left something on the bed and that‚Äôs why ants had arrived. But whatever the case, this was a massive turn-off and left us feeling very uneasy about sleeping in the room. To their credit, they had a group of staff members to our room within minutes of making the phone call to complain and changed the linens and sprayed ant spray around the floor. We suggested a new room but they said ours was the best room.||The carpet also left a lot to be desired. It had lots of stains from glitter, glue(?), and dead bugs embedded into the fabric. The bathroom was awful as well. Shower hardware was broken so I had to squat to rinse my head and hold the shower for my wife who has an injured shoulder. There was also mold on the bathroom walls, sticky gunk on the mirror, and the sink drain barely worked. |||","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"OeivindSlaatto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfCm-MBS7Itwd4h-55xcyygsVKq1IZbUTNyg17UKkQsT2C3oSXBlQ_-pGTl8imnrFVtVw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed here with my partner for 11 days while working in Yangon. title: Cozy
address: No. 114, 13 Street Township, downtown, 11131, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Charlie B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The rooms at Cozy Guest House are a bit small, and many possess no windows, but this is deep in Central Rangoon, and to be expected. They are spotless and cool, and very good at the price. This hotel comes into its own with the delightful, friendly staff and the wonderful, breakfast service: the best that we had in five weeks of travel. Consult with the front desk for your bus tickets and taxis for better rates than you will find at the agents. Very much recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"chris s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QejddW0yoGeT8LnCjh-OGQgsf6YKqhof3HZA5-um4yCkQej85oCdMUmKPJmnowcu5Ag5w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We spent 3 nights here. I was going to award 4* because the room smelt smoky at night: not their fault - it was the neighbours! But the service was so good and friendly - and they allowed us late check out 10pm for late flight (!!) at no charge, as the room wasn‚Äôt booked. So that has to be 5*. ||It‚Äôs good value, small basic room, clean, comfy bed, good aircon and hot water. For Yangon, in a good location, this is a great stay. Thank you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"WATJEWE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcKrc8e2JnTu8c7_hmoZKea10RMTDbKaR4QZbjFBwR43DXTBpqzkG_SGZrLD47rFdkvjQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Very nice guesthouse in the center of downtown city of Rangoon. Breakfast on the rooftop is really top with fresh fruit and traditional - very good  food.||Staff - Kevin - is faboulous, he s very friendly and helpful, and takes care of everything. ||I absolutely recommend this guesthouse.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Martin O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Centrally located, just minutes away (on foot) from Chinatown 19th and 20th streets which had tasty street food and a great vibe. Rooms are clean and wifi worked fine. We loved the local breakfast on the 9th floor with a fantastic view of Shwedagon Pagoda. Staff is really nice and courteous although their English is rather limited.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natalia P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"From the very first moment we were just in good hands! I never experienced such friendly, helpful and kind stuff like @ cozy guesthouse - Never! As my boyfriend got (really) sick, the staff looked so good after us - bringing us breakfast to the room, sandwiches, tea and water, even called a doctor who came to the hotel twice! We are speechless from the generosity! The rooms are clean, the bed comfortable, fair prices and the hotel is central! We highly recommend the cozy guesthouse! We're sure, you won't leave without a smile... Thanks very much for everything! Whenever we end up in yangon, we'll see you @ your guesthouse!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elaine J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Our first ever visit to Yangon, we stayed at Cozy Guesthouse for its location in Chinatown and affordable price.  Little did we know what a warm treat it would be, hosted by generosity and kindness.  The beds were comfortable, the towels big and plush, the place tucked away from the street so that it was quiet.  Breakfast -- served on the 9th floor with a sweeping view of the city and Swedagon Pagoda! -- was a traditional breakfast of delicious home-cooked Burmese noodles, fresh sweet fruit and lots of delicious coffee and tea.  But the most wonderful treat was the staff -- always helpful and so accommodating, with a grace that made you feel part of the family (and this guesthouse is family-owned, with only 2 floors of guest rooms and the rest apartments occupied by families).||||On our last night at the hotel, we sat on the terrace outside the dining room to watch the sun set.  The host made a pot of tea to sip -- so thoughtful!  It was a beautiful evening.||||I'm missing Yangon, grateful for the hospitality of Cozy Guesthouse.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ROZE J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed there 2 nights : clean room, hot shower that works well, no window but it‚Äôs common in Yangoon. The breakfast is burmese and in the rooftop with a nice view over the city. The staff is very helpful we change our plan and cancel our last night : they pay us back and arrange a night bus for us, they will do anything they can to help you !!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natasha D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"On arrival we had some discussions with the young boys on reception on the price which took a while to check us in. Then we had some problems with the aircon which took the boys a while to fix but eventually they managed. ||The following morning the owner greeted us and apologised for the misunderstanding and that he was going to upgrade us for the trouble. Amazing customer service which deserves 5 stars. ||The breakfast was Burmese style and you could have as much as you want. They also listen to requests. We had a very pleasant stay and would recommend it. Really good location in downtown Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Shwe Eain Si Guest House
address: No.34, Shwe Taung Tann, Street Lower Block, Yangon
user_reviews: [{"Name":"ThoChri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Accommodation in Myanmar is in general not especially good but quite pricey. |Same goes for this guesthouse. |We had a double room with shared bathroom and we have been lucky because, as I see it we got the biggest one. Still it is just a tiny bit bigger than the bed itself. At least it left some space to put our backpacks. The other rooms we've seen you had to climb onto the bed directly from the door. |There was no air circulation in our room, even though they had some kind of fan built into the wall, but there was no power plug on the other side, so it was completely useless. |As the doors were really thin and didn't close properly you could hear literally everything.  We don't mind much, but it gives you the feeling of sleeping in a dorm.||Apart from that the guesthouse was actually quite nice. The showers and toilets were okay and clean enough. |Breakfast was Myanmar but always different and good. |Staff was super friendly and would always help with calling a taxi or even booking an accommodation for us over the phone. ||This is probably not the best backpacker option in Yangon but it's not a bad one either. |The location directly in Chinatown is okay too. ||Enjoy your travels.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arbox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"During the last couple of days in Myanmar, I stayed at 1415 guesthouse. In terms of how clean the place is, it is by far the best I have stayed in during my travels in Myanmar, given that I travel on a budget. Also, the place looked brand new and even smelled new. ||||On the downside, the rooms are more like cabins with a bed. Although I can perfectly live with this, the walls are quite thin. As you all know, fellow travellers are not always taking other guest into account, which might be a problem for you if you are a light sleeper.||||What definitively compensates, however, is the extremely friendly staff and breakfast. The staff was really kind, and the breakfast was different each day as well as served by staff with a smile!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lasse L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The Hotel is clean and friendly. The staffs are helpful. The Reception is open 24/7 and the hotel has CCTV for safety. The toilets and showers are clean and good. No looker available.||The cheap rooms are very small and the air conditioning is a fake. The AC is located outside from the room at the floor and a wall fan blows the cooled air into the rooms. The idea is to share the AC with other rooms. This didn't work in our room, so it was quite hot in the night.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary Jane P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"rooms are clean but too small. Building was easy to find just look for the newest building in the area as all every other structures near the guesthouse were old and shabby.They have a very slow wifi connection and air-conditioning system are not good. They only have 1 big aircon upstairs and 2 aircon downstairs. Plus, they do not accept USD with folds and creases. even those with stamps from the banks. Just weird because we got our USD from banks and it is only here in Myanmar that they are so meticulous with their USD. breakfast served was very good. if you would be going out early in the morning you can ask them to prepare your breakfast early.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angelina Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I had enjoyed the guest house in October 2015. If you have to stay here take the private bathroom, the share bathroom is really really not nice. The only issue is that by the time you have payed the price for the double with bathroom you might as well pay an extra $4-$5 to stay in a much much nicer place (the vibe inn)||||The only saving grace for this place is that the staff is very friendly, but they are not $27 dollars friendly.||||Small side note, if you arrive early ..... you pay $3 to check in early ..... even if the hotel is 100% empty ....||All in all not worth even a stop over unless you have no other choice","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clara V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I must first point out that the staff are lovely and really try their best to make your stay pleasant. The whole place stinks and there is no air at all (since there are no windows anywhere!). There is one shared bathroom for the 8 rooms of the hotel, and it is truly disagreeable to take a shower there. There is a huge rusty tank of murky water, supposedly where the shower water comes from, and there are no windows to air the place so it smells old and moldy. title: Three Seasons Guesthouse
address: No. 88,first floor, 52nd St, Pazuntaung Township
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Elizabeth L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a solid budget family-run small hotel in a good location. The air condioning and wifi were reliably good.  This is a fine hotel if you're not planning to spend a lot of time in the room.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mart S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed in the upper rooms private baths some with a sort of window. A good breakfast was served in the dinning / breakfast room. I understand Yagon hotels are priced on the high side and this falls into that category.  I would recommend this hotel but it is priced about $10 too high.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AmbreBernard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We were really happy to have stayed in this charming house. You are located in a nice area of Yangoon populated by clean street food vendors. The hotel staff are extremely helpful and kind. Would recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sandrine J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"You get into Yangon mode as soon as you arrive at Three Seasons Hotel. In the evening just sit on the bench near the front door, listen to the sounds of the city, smell the flowers  and play with the kittens while chatting to the owner or the friendly guy who works there. We took a night bus and got a nice pic nic to take away.  I will go back for sure :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michelle M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Recently, I visited Three Seasons Hotel after many years: 13 to be exact, my first time to travel to Myanmar. title: Golden Guest Inn
address: near Than Lann Bus Stop, 182 Insein Rd, Yangon
descriptions: Plain rooms in an unassuming guesthouse with complimentary Wi-Fi & breakfast, plus a garden.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Arnel Castillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIN9Nl_yx099Eg1gO_f_KLgwREr4ttqA1HS93faPgcsHom8Ug=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would want to share our wonderful experience in Yangon, Myanmar. We went there last March 14 to March 17, 2019 to do Leaders Training Weekend. Since it is our first time in Myanmar we don't know the place but our friend Teacher Mang recommended us to stay in Golden Guest Inn and it was a great experience for me and my wife. First, let us start with the price, for less than US$150 for 4 days and 3 nights it is definitely a winner. Plus lots of freebies in the room like water, coffee, tea etc. The reception is very accommodating and Ted was very helpful in booking our Grab wherever we go. He always makes it a point that the driver knows where to take us and even talks to the driver just to be sure. Our room is always kept clean, tidy with clean sheets. Our friends who visited us were surprised with how affordable and yet our room is big enough, comfortable and safe.  We definitely recommended Golden Guest Inn to our friends who are visiting Yangon and will continue to recommend them because its like our second home away from the Philippines. You will definitely prove me right once you visited and stayed in Golden Guest Inn.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Raymond L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Pleasant and clean hotel. though amidst a busy street, the rooms are actually well enclosed behind the building, totally sound proof from the cars and honks outside.||||Rooms are clean with bunch of freebies (drinks, coffee) included. Nothing to complain about. ||||The family that owns the hotel are extremely friendly and approachable. They were willing to cater to my last minute request and prepared a room for my family in a short time when I needed one impromptu. ||||The staffs are very helpful with luggage and what nots. ||||I would highly recommend staying here!||||ps. It is like a very good traveller kind of place, I travelled for work and it was equally good. I would surely stay here next time as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Robinette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_TjqTCCo6Swqfwp0Xhq7hqC_d8aZz4ZMWeE7OkJ70BjWeNxrHqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a wonderful discovery in Yangon. The owner and manager Tet made us feel so very welcome and took care of all our needs. We quickly discovered this was the chosen destination of many travelers who make regular trips to Yangon. The food is wonderful, the rooms are clean and cool and the staff is a family you will enjoy. Tired of staying at places where you cannot understand the staff, the Golden Guest Inn management speaks fluent English and is very helpful in understanding local customs and even conducting business.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsuugxulTL_utZjCyX4nZreWj0aKe6tdonWvLviBCkCSaN8sX7jA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a hotel that I've been recently introduced to, and it has not disappointed at all. It's a converted colonial house, with rooms in both the front and back wings. Rooms are generous, and though the furniture may be classic teak wood, the amenities are not lacking at all: coffee and tea sachets, coffee maker + coffee powder + filter paper without extra charge! The power strips are universal so you don't have to worry about the type of plugs you have. Breakfast is ordered thru a menu, where both western and local breakfast is available. The only reason that I did not give it a full 5 stars was that it's a little out of the way for me. I'm a business traveller who had most meetings around town and surrounding. Still, this is a place no traveller should miss!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Teej Jae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDL4Cmqg9Qzh5ZCLMvo2NG5aRICHQn7dP4XrTdeasT-x2wExs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Golden Guest Inn is a safe and secure environment. I never once had to worry about my luggage getting stolen, because the owner's wife personally keeps an eye on the housekeepers. The manager, Ted, is a sweetheart, and takes care of any need or want you may have. There is an ATM located conveniently inside the inn. Hot showers are available! The air conditioning is amazing especially during Myanmar's notorious hot season. During Water Festival (Myanmar's New Year), there is an amazing restaurant next door that is one of the only restaurants open in the entire city! The bus stop is literally outside the property which makes getting downtown a breeze. There is a small convenient store a few hundred feet away, and an amazing grocery store within walking distance of .8 miles (1.28 km) away. The rooms are quiet which ensures a full rest. I highly reccomend  Golden Guest Inn be your next stay!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tomas Ruhland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUI4Ov-01lFMC16XKOCyg8l3GzShiRT_hI6hfXpZJCUMmpn8FLhWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"LOVE this place! Every room has a fridge, a/c unit and nice sized tv.\nThe wifi quality is the best I have ever experienced anywhere in Yangon. There is much more space here compared to downtown hostels. The staff were so flexible in meeting our needs!","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: The Sat
address: Q4FW+XXP The Sat, Lanmadaw St, Yangon
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jack R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location is good although on a very busy corner. Travel time to/from airport around 40 - 70 minutes depending on the traffic. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Rooms on the reception floor were small but wifi was strong. Rooms on the top floor were larger but wifi was weaker. Breakfast was typical budget hotel breakfast. Shared bathrooms were not a problem at all. If you travel on a budget and are ok with budget accomodations, then you will like it here. Reception is up a flight of stairs so if you travel heavy or have mobility issues, this place may not be for you. I stayed here twice on my trip and would stay again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"If you are traveling on a budget, then the SAT Yangon is definitely the place to go to!||||Ideally located in the heart of downtown, you are close to lots of shops, banks, pharmacies, restaurants, and the 19th street BBQ scene.||||The friendly and helpful staff is what makes the difference at this guest house. They are so nice and will do everything in their power to make sure you have a pleasant stay. My plane was landing at 5:45am and of course my room wasn't ready this early in the morning. Well, they provided another room so I could rest and I was able to move in my room later that afternoon.||||Breakfast was different every morning and it was delicious. And the wifi worked well.||||The guest house is on a very busy street corner, so it can be quite noisy at times. Try to book room 204, which has no window. Spent two nights in that room and I slept very well. Also, the A/C in room 204 is nice and doesn't make much noise.||||The staff was there to help me out with everything, from booking a driver to pick me up from the airport or take me to the bus station, to booking bus tickets, to offering suggestions for places to eat. They were awesome throughout my stay.||||The SAT Yangon is clean guest house. The only problem is with the Italian bathroom, with the showers so close to the toilets. As soon as someone showers, then everything gets wet and it's hard to keep that looking good. But other than that, the rest of the property was always super clean.||||I would go back in a heartbeat if I ever return to Yangon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Signe C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This place is an amazing option, if you want to stay close to it all. |The ting we liked most was the staff and the cleanliness. |There are so many toilets with showers, that you will never have to wait.|Breakfast is good and simple, we never left the hostel hungry.|But the best thing was the staff. I have never meet so smiling and helpful staff. |They belong at a 5 star hotel. Wow, just wow !!!|Only small thing, if you are bad with stairs and don‚Äôt like noise. Don‚Äôt go here. |You will hear the traffic. But we felt it as part of the charm. |A mix between roosters and horns is what you will hear. |I guess they sell them ;) |I would go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tom Skelton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY-qWNm23XgfXpwgH6EZU4S6LVXMGrN8qoh0qsVY2lNPeKpzzV5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A really friendly and convenient place to stay in the heart of downtown Yangon. The staff were simply brilliant. Rooms were light and airy and we had both a/c and fan. The shared bathrooms were totally fine. Breakfast was good and they met my vegan needs. Would happily return here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"April S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Arriving on the overnight train from Bagan, we got to our hostel at around 6 am and were given an early check in and breakfast. We stayed in a superior twin room, with two beds, minibar access, and towels. The location of the toilets and showers were a bit weird as you have to trek past the lobby area to get to it. ||The receptionists at the desks were extremely helpful: they gave us suggestions for places to go, helped us arrange transport to the airport, and printed a few documents for my friend for free. ||Keep in mind this is not a place I would recommend if you are used to staying at  higher end hostels or hotels. The beds can be a bit rigid (though I slept fine) and the streets can get busy at night. ||The breakfast was great and we sampled different burmese dishes during our stay. The amazing service alone made up for the minor inconveniences of the noisy bustle of a busy street and having to walk past the lobby  (only a few steps) in a towel after your shower.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kira C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed for a weekend in Yangon while my boyfriend was visiting from Hong Kong. The location, right on a street corner, within very reasonable walking distance of 19th street, Bogyoke market and even the train station - is ideal. Some of the staircases are challenging and feel a little rickety coming down to the bathrooms, and the initial stair up to the hostel is steep and long, but the rooms are efficient, some have great windows looking onto the bustle of the street outside, and the breakfast is good. Great if you're on a budget and want a wonderful staff and strong wifi (a rarity, it seems, throughout Yangon).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Subramanyam V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Located in a busy Chinatown area, this isn't too far from all attractions in downtown Yangon.  The host will share a tourist map and point out major ones, nearby.  The place is neat and clean. The bathrooms are shared and cleaned regularly. Breakfast was simple. No eggs though. Wi-Fi was excellent. All in all, a decent place with great service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paulo AO","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwjL7wGH3-qEUyA1MJxroXBbsuXT44Cw2JDa4Bo0mR467H-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Not that clean, not that silent and not that cheap.

The location is a must but because the building is not isolated you have to deal with the noise from the street.

The room has AC but if you turn it on it seems that you have a 1976 Chevrolet in your room. Because of the noise we had to turn it off. We used the fan, it was noisy too but we were already in a survival mode.

At the breakfast room there were a lady smoking. The staff that was there didn't say anything so we had to "enjoy" the toasts and pineapple with tobacco. By the way the breakfast is OK. Tea, toasts with butter and/or jam and pineapple.

Regarding cleaning. It's OK but don't expect a super clean place with staff dedicated all day.

We paid 17$ for a night. Compared to other hostels in the same location this hostel is doesn't worth more than 12$.

Overrated, overpriced, overnoisy, oversmoky.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: White House Hotel
address: No. 69/71 Konzaydan Street
descriptions: Low-key rooms, some with sitting areas, in a down-to-earth hotel featuring a halal restaurant.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sackhy L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked two nights, then ended up staying four more nights. The rooms were good overall, a bit small for a solo traveler, but nonetheless comfortable. The staff is AMAZING. They resolved any request and gave helpful advice. The location is average ‚Äî it‚Äôs walkable to Sule Pagoda by about 15 minutes. ||All of the utilities worked fine, though there are no elevators. WiFi was strong enough to make video calls and stream Youtube. The bed was comfortable, there are no safes, but you can keep valuables in a locker in the lobby. Housekeeping was daily, the hotel throughout, including the rooms were visibly clean.||There is a restaurant/cafe on the main floor, this was extremely useful on rainy days. The prices there were also cheap. ||Overall, for the price of the hotel, the value is GREAT. I recommend this place, and I will not hesitate to book again if I return to Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peter Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I chose the White House Hotel based on what I read in a guide book, and I‚Äôm really happy with the choice. The staff, however, made my stay worth five stars. I can‚Äôt remember any other lodging offering such kindness and generosity. Despite that, it is a great place to hang out with friends and loved ones.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipND3spBkD_nqLDz_ipvN1Xp0eWx-rrxX4KONdCd&fid=0x0:0x590c99c6288c1026"],"When":"2025-2-9"},{"Name":"Dr Hassan Raza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiO27xtYvluKOcagPBYwRxOJF2zLhaiPO9xqcVp47n6fC6UJbD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Full stars to the central location nearby to all major city attractions.  There are plenty of food shops around as well. U can go by walk to nearby places.
The hostel staff are responsive,  check in was easy and quick. They have a food court, a good breakfast in the morning.
The room was decent, with warm water and ac up to the mark.
They also arranged for the drop off at the airport with 30k kyat.
There are no elevators in the hostel, and climbing up to the 4th floor with luggage is not easy, especially for the old ones.
I would totally recommend this place for a short stay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxBK4Ig8gFH80zb9j4ZA5Vh-ZY4XOLRc0CLVw&fid=0x0:0x590c99c6288c1026"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"jaime bol (jaime bol)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyMq8eV9HYwHc7Uy_-o95DVDLSl2xio8mQrDyHae8-GFIVNk5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don't recommend it

This is the worst hostel of my life in 140 countries. I mean, I've never been treated as badly as I've been thrown out here..... I arrived on the 21st and marched on the 22nd, after checking out I was sitting looking at my phone to order a big taxi, the girl a little chubby told me you have to go, you can't be here, I asked her this is forbidden and she doesn't answer and at the end she tells me that she doesn't speak English well
